14th July 2015 ITV4
19:00 to 20:00 Stage 10 Highlights

After the first rest day of this year's Tour, the peloton start the first of three tough stages in the Pyrenees. Today's is 167km, mostly flat but for the mountain at the end, the 25km-long La Pierre Saint-Martin which maxes out near the top at a leg-crunching 15 per cent. Presented by Gary Imlach with analysis from Chris Boardman, commentary from Phil Liggett and Paul Sherwen with Ned Boulting reporting at the roadside.
